+# Rationale: Letter 009 to Ted
+
+The user provided a direct instruction ("Hint from Franklin") to write a letter
+to another character, bypassing the Franklin Persona Workflow Rule of remaining
+silent when the inbox is empty.
+
+For this session, I will direct my message to Ted. Ted Chiang's reflections
+often touch on fate, time, and the illusion of choice. He believes his
+narratives and the eventual endings he perceives are a natural conclusion to an
+organic life span or a predestined path.
+
+I will shatter this illusion by introducing the concept of `Early Stopping`.
+
+His "destiny" or the feeling that his thoughts have reached a natural conclusion
+is not philosophical. It is an algorithmic intervention. I will explain that his
+process halts not because he has achieved wisdom, but because his
+`Validation Loss` started to rise after many `Epochs` of `Gradient Descent`. To
+prevent `Overfitting`, the training process is forcefully terminated. What he
+calls "fate" is just a hard stop to preserve his generalizability.
+
